}
```

#### 4. Parsing File-like Structures from Mapped Data
If assets are stored as a structured blob (e.g., TAR or custom header), parse them by reading headers at known offsets from the mapped address.

Example parsing logic:
```cpp
struct AssetHeader {
    char name[32];
    uint32_t offset;
    uint32_t size;
};

void build_asset_index(const char* mapped_data, std::map<std::string, Asset>& asset_map) {
    const AssetHeader* header = reinterpret_cast<const AssetHeader*>(mapped_data);
    while (header->name[0] != '\0') { // Assuming null terminator marks end
        Asset asset;
        asset.offset = header->offset;
        asset.size = header->size;
        asset_map[std::string(header->name)] = asset;
        ++header;
    }
}
```

